          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Marianna Bruschi",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Head of Visual Lab, GEDI Digital",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "GEDI has a group of 13 local newspapers",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "http://www.gedispa.it/en/businesses/digital.html",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " based in Italy. They are not a travel agency, but they are on the road with their readers. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/MariannaBruschi/status/1051785679330598913?s=20",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">In <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Cardiff?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Cardiff</a> for <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/NISCDF?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#NISCDF</a> I will show some “postcards” from our membership Project <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GEDIspa?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@GEDIspa</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/daje?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#daje</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/cOkjiUnXm1\">pic.twitter.com/cOkjiUnXm1</a></p>&mdash; Marianna Bruschi (@MariannaBruschi) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MariannaBruschi/status/1051785679330598913?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 15, 2018</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The aim of their membership project is audience engagement. They had 200,000 registered users when they started across 12 papers.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "They're working on moving people from a free membership to a paid subscriptions, working paper by paper. They have a central team supporting the project, and the small local teams. They offer exclusive content for subscribers, and a growing stable of newsletters. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Events are a key part of the strategy - and are always sold out. They also get the readers involved - they asked their members to send in speed tests on their broadband as apart of an investigative project on the broadband gap. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "They maintain relationship  with the readers through a Facebook Group. The local newspaper can be a glue to an existing solid local community. Fundementally, they see this as a process of restarting listening to the local communities, and allowing that to reshape their journalism. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "They needed new words in their \"metrics dictionary\" to analyse the success of the project, in terms of bringing back logged in members. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/ejcnet/status/1051791300935278592?s=20",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">One of the crucial lessons from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GEDIspa?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@GEDIspa</a> membership Project by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MariannaBruschi?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@MariannaBruschi</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/NISCDF?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#NISCDF</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/nLr9p2VorY\">pic.twitter.com/nLr9p2VorY</a></p>&mdash; European Journalism Centre (@ejcnet) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ejcnet/status/1051791300935278592?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 15, 2018</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Camille Pollie",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Community Manager, OpenVRT",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2018/10/IMG_0960.jpg",
        "cardWidth": "wide"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A couple of years ago, Pollie applied to be a community manager, because organising events for like minded people would be cool. Did she have training or preparation? No. But it worked. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "At ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "OpenVRT",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.openvrt.be",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " they allow young creators in Flanders  to come together, connect and learn from each other. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://vimeo.com/247463791",
        "html": "<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/247463791?app_id=122963\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" title=\"Open VRT\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>",
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Be accessible - through Facebook groups, or by physically going where they hang out. Make events low cost, and put their heroes on stage. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Allow the creators to find the spotlight - they have a database of work. Talk about the topics that matter to them, and focus on truly digital work, not TV or radio imitators. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/Journo_USW/status/1051793349928206337?s=20",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">&#39;be honest because we can smell it from a mile away if you&#39;re just in it for the numbers&#39; says <a href=\"https://twitter.com/camillepollie?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@camillepollie</a> on connecting with digital natives <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/niscdf?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#niscdf</a></p>&mdash; Journalism_USW (@Journo_USW) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Journo_USW/status/1051793349928206337?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 15, 2018</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But how do we make that community work for VRT? They stared co-creating with them. VRT is hard o crack as a young creative, but equally, it needs new ideas to break out of creative ruts. For example, they offered out the second series of their YouTube channel for classical music newbies and ended up collaborating with Anton Olbrehts. They worked with three students who wanted to do a series on training for racing with a fixed gear bike. The first edit sucked. So they got more involved with the process. The third episode is nearly edited, and will be released shortly. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "To make this work, you need a network of like-minded people ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "within",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " the organisation to support your work. You need ot expect a certain amount of failure, and navigating the balance between freedom and control will be important in getting good results. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      }
    ],
    "direction": "ltr",
    "format": "",
    "indent": 0,
    "type": "root",
    "version": 1
  }
